    en: "New York Labor Law Section 194-b, effective September 17, 2023, requires private employers with four or more employees to include a good-faith salary or hourly-wage range on every job posting, promotion announcement, and transfer opportunity posted for positions that are physically performed at least in part in New York. Commission-based roles must be identified. The range must be what the employer would actually pay — not a placeholder. The NYS Department of Labor enforces the statute with civil penalties up to $3,000 per violation. Employees have the right to see internal postings on the same terms. Separate laws bar retaliation for discussing wages with coworkers (Labor Law 215)."
